  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Comprehensive Care Project to Strengthen Communities with People Living with HIV/AIDS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Comprehensive Care Project to Strengthen Communities with People Living with HIV/AIDS will serve 300 families, including those whose members are people living with HIV/AIDS (PLWHA) in the villages of Mae Salong Nai and Pa Ha in Mae Salong sub-districts and the villages of San Na Yao and Wieng Sa in Sri Kham sub-districts of Mae Chan district, Chiang Rai Province. The project will include 100 original families and 200 additional families through Heifer&#x2019;s Pass on the Gift (POG) process. Their capacity will be enhanced through the Values-Based Holistic Community Development approach. The project will help participants establish four original self-help groups (SHGs) and at least eight POG SHGs.The 100 original families will be provided with 100 cows and 250 piglets. In addition, the capacity of SHGs will be strengthened with training on Heifer&#x2019;s 12 Cornerstones; group management; savings management; improved animal management; sustainable agriculture techniques; natural resource management; and exchange forums among PLWHAs, their families and relatives, and other community members. The original families will pass on all of the received inputs, equal in quality and quantity, and knowledge gained to the POG families. To ensure effective project management, transparency and mutual learning, a project management committee will be formed and functional with representatives from the SHGs, project partners and Heifer, as well as other stakeholders.</narrative>
  </description>
